15.4 Governance Process (Institutional Version)
Governance follows a predictable and transparent five-step model:
1.	Proposal Drafting
A contributor drafts a structured governance proposal.
2.	Public Publication
The proposal is made accessible for review by the community and institutions.
3.	Consultation Period
Feedback is collected from curators, advisors, partners, and governance bodies.
4.	Multi-sig Validation
The Multi-sig Committee approves the proposal (3/5 signatures).
5.	Archiving & Documentation
The decision is publicly archived and included in governance records.
This institutional model mirrors real-world organisational processes.
